result.adr_address: 70 Peel St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Brunch Club

reviews.text:
Food here was fabulous 🥰😋🥞🥬🥔🌽🥕🍳🥪🥘🥛🍹🍯🍴🍮🍩
Been here for the first time and I luv it sooo much!! The egg Benedict w asparagus was amazing, they just match perfectly 🥰❤️ Huge fan for now☺️☺️☺️
And the chocolate waffle tastes awesome 👏🏼😋🥰😳☺️❤️
Highly recommended for a try!!

We were looking for a quiet place to sit down and chat on a workday night. And walked into this place. ordered the pancakes for dessert. If you were looking for anything fluffy, buttery, this isn’t the place. It’s more of a solid and firm texture and fills you up quickly.
Always a pleasure to spend time there. Food is great, environment is peaceful and staff is AH MAH ZING! I could easily come here every Sunday

10% Service Charge is now added on the menu. Prices have increased at approximately between 10-15%. These are okay if portions and quality are much better. 

Food portion has gone smaller
Food quality has gone from BAD to WORSE! 

Stale Breads. Bad coffee. Salad leaves are limped! How could you be wrong with pancakes? So easy to make. But these guys use frozen pancakes to be cooked or reheat again. It’s so obvious that they use frozen ones - I buy them sometimes at the store!
It was a nice place to eat and chat. I have a great time with my friends here. Go and give a try this place. I would suggest the frittata. See the pic.
